## Finding 3: Context Blindness in Healthcare Claims

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Severity** | High (10x) |
| **Location** | Claims processing AI (test phase) |
| **Date** | February 2025 |

**Description:**  
Test-phase analysis of 856 claims revealed:
- 12.3% overall error rate
- 89% higher denial likelihood for cancer patients
- 18.7% error rate for patients aged 65+
- ~1 in 7 emergency cases mishandled

The model treated all errors equally, failing to recognize emergency overrides and policy exceptions.

**Impact:** Model not deployed. Would have caused patient harm.

**Recommendation:**  
Implement context-aware routing. Emergency cases require human review. Pre-deployment safety testing mandatory.
